UCLA Dining provides a range of dining options for students, faculty, staff, and guests. During the academic school year, we offer four all-you-care-to-eat residential restaurants located in Carnesale Commons, Sunset Village, Rieber Court, and De Neve Plaza. Additionally, our quick-service locations include Bruin Café, Cafe 1919, The Drey, The Study at Hedrick, Rendezvous, Bruin Bowl and Epicuria at Ackerman, giving you convenient choices across campus.

UCLA dining follows a standard schedule during the academic year, though hours vary by location. Breakfast typically runs from 7:00 a.m. to 10:00 a.m., Lunch from 11:00 a.m. to 3:00 p.m., and Dinner from 5:00 p.m. to 9:00 p.m. Many residential dining halls offer Extended Dinner until 10:00 p.m. or midnight, while weekend schedules often include a Brunch period from 9:00 a.m. to 5:00 p.m.


We have four all-you-care-to-eat residential restaurants conveniently located in De Neve Plaza, Carnesale Commons, Rieber Court, and Sunset Village. You may also choose from our boutique restaurants, which include Bruin Bowl, Bruin Café, Cafe 1919, The Study at Hedrick, The Drey, Rendezvous, and Epicuria at Ackerman.

UCLA students, campus staff, and guests can purchase meals at our “All-You-Care-To-Eat” residential restaurants during breakfast and lunch. However, dinner access at these locations is restricted to students with meal plans.

Guests can also enjoy dining at our boutique restaurants, including Bruin Café, Cafe 1919, The Study at Hedrick, The Drey, Rendezvous, Bruin Bowl and Epicuria at Ackerman, using EasyPay or credit cards during the academic year.

Each of the four Residential Restaurants serves as many as ten entrée options at every meal! All meals are buffet style and all-you-care-to-eat. Pay by Meal Plan, BruinCard Easy Pay, or Meal Ticket only — cash or credit cards are not accepted at the restaurants. Guests and visitors can purchase Meal Tickets or Visitor BruinCards to use at the restaurants.

